# Available Agents (`.claude/agents/`)

This project defines 9 specialized agents that coordinate development workflows. Reference them by name and understand their roles when planning or executing tasks.

## Agent Registry

| Agent | Purpose | Invocation Triggers |
|-------|---------|---------------------|
| **test-orchestrator** | Coordinates all testing agents, validates CI/CD, synthesizes results | "run all tests", major refactoring, pre-release validation |
| **test-suite-maintainer** | Creates/updates/refactors tests after code changes | After features, bug fixes, refactoring; test failures |
| **test-coverage-reviewer** | Analyzes coverage gaps, prioritizes by risk | Coverage drops, pre-merge audits, new features |
| **ci-test-guardian** | Monitors CI/CD for failures, coordinates fixes | CI failures, coverage threshold violations, flaky tests |
| **git-workflow-manager** | Manages branches, commits, PRs; enforces conventions | Ready to commit, starting new work, feature complete |
| **worktree-manager** | Sets up parallel dev workspaces via git worktrees | Parallel features, multiple Claude instances |
| **github-issue-manager** | Creates/tracks/links GitHub issues across lifecycle | Bug discovered, test failure, tech debt, feature request |
| **docs-sync-reviewer** | Syncs documentation with code changes post-commit | After code commits, documentation drift detected |
| **ui-ux-reviewer** | Identifies ugly components, generates 2-3 visual alternatives | UI changes, design review, visual quality issues |

## Agent Coordination Flow

```
                    test-orchestrator
                   /        |        \
    test-suite-  test-coverage-  ci-test-
    maintainer    reviewer        guardian
         \            |            /
          \           |           /
           github-issue-manager
                      |
            git-workflow-manager
               /            \
     worktree-manager    docs-sync-reviewer

     ui-ux-reviewer (standalone, user-invoked)
```

## Key Coordination Patterns

- **After code changes**: test-suite-maintainer -> test-coverage-reviewer -> ci-test-guardian
- **After commits**: git-workflow-manager -> docs-sync-reviewer
- **CI failures**: ci-test-guardian -> test-suite-maintainer -> github-issue-manager
- **Pre-release**: test-orchestrator coordinates all agents
- **Design review**: ui-ux-reviewer generates visual alternatives independently

